Moreover, the distinction between organic and conventional green tea categories is another critical segment in the market. The rise of health-conscious consumers and the growing awareness of the potential health risks associated with pesticides and chemicals in conventional agriculture have fueled the demand for organic green tea products. Consumers are actively seeking organic options that are free from harmful chemicals and promote environmental sustainability. Market players focusing on organic green tea offerings are likely to capitalize on this trend and attract a niche segment of consumers who prioritize health and sustainability in their purchasing decisions. alongside organic options, conventional green tea remains popular among a broader consumer base looking for affordable and accessible green tea products.

The distribution channel segment is also a key component of the global green tea market, influencing the availability and accessibility of products to consumers. Supermarkets/hypermarkets, convenience stores, and other retail outlets play a crucial role in reaching a wide consumer base and driving sales of green tea products. The convenience and variety offered by supermarkets/hypermarkets make them a popular choice for consumers looking to purchase green tea products during their regular shopping trips. On the other hand, convenience stores provide quick and easy access to green tea products for on-the-go consumers. The evolving distribution landscape, including the significant growth of online retail channels, is reshaping the market dynamics by offering alternative avenues for consumers to purchase green tea products conveniently.

